 in coming to him; it was only a problem of a different sort.
 He could deal with a question of loyalties, at least in the near term.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I figured out his identity, wrote Lex.
 It wasn't difficult once I started looking at the people around you.
 He watched her face as she read that, then took the notebook from her again
 before she had a chance to respond.
 You're starting to feel sympathy towards him.
 You think that you understand where he's coming from.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lois shrugged, then nodded.
 He's not perfect, she wrote back.
 But I think that I know where he's coming from now.
 We've been talking a lot lately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He murdered a man in cold blood, wrote Lex, but Lois was already shaking
 her head.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He regrets it, she wrote back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What else will he come to regret? asked Lex.
 We're talking about the fate of the world.
 You know that there's no stopping him if he goes rogue.
 Even if the chance is slim, it's a chance weighed against the total destruction
